1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:02,544
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

2
00:00:02,627 --> 00:00:05,588
["Mr. Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,591 --> 00:00:09,801
♪ <i>Fix it</i> ♪

4
00:00:10,802 --> 00:00:12,887
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

5
00:00:12,971 --> 00:00:15,849
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

6
00:00:16,808 --> 00:00:20,937
The husband of Mrs. Santos
met with Aldrin Galang.

7
00:00:21,020 --> 00:00:24,482
[Mercado] <i>After one week,</i>
<i>her husband was found dead.</i>

8
00:00:24,566 --> 00:00:27,068
[Red] <i>The nun in the convent survived.</i>

9
00:00:27,152 --> 00:00:28,570
[Mongki] <i>The one who fell</i>
<i>from the bell tower?</i>

10
00:00:28,653 --> 00:00:29,904
She recognized me.

11
00:00:29,988 --> 00:00:32,115
[Emerson] Atoy? Is this one
of your secret missions?

12
00:00:32,866 --> 00:00:34,367
[Aldrin] I'll come back in two days.

13
00:00:34,451 --> 00:00:36,453
When I come back, you should
have your contribution ready.

14
00:00:36,536 --> 00:00:38,371
Yes, boss. No problem, boss.

15
00:00:38,455 --> 00:00:40,248
I'm looking for Janine.

16
00:00:40,331 --> 00:00:42,333
[Audrey] <i>She suddenly left home.</i>

17
00:00:42,417 --> 00:00:44,335
[Atoy] <i>I'm doing surveillance here.</i>

18
00:00:44,419 --> 00:00:46,880
- [Emerson] <i>Huh?</i>
- [Atoy] <i>The person I'm looking for…</i>

19
00:00:46,963 --> 00:00:48,673
<i>kind of hostile, bro.</i>

20
00:00:48,757 --> 00:00:51,801
[nun] <i>I don't know any nuns</i>
<i>named Sister Norma.</i>

21
00:00:51,885 --> 00:00:53,011
[Red] <i>You're from the same congregation.</i>

22
00:00:53,094 --> 00:00:55,430
I recognize the habits you wear!
Where is she?

23
00:00:55,513 --> 00:00:56,848
[Ibyang] Hey! You're bad!

24
00:00:56,931 --> 00:00:58,558
Why are you bullying a nun?

25
00:00:58,641 --> 00:01:00,977
You'll go to hell!

26
00:01:01,061 --> 00:01:04,064
Hey, little kid, why are you meddling?

27
00:01:04,147 --> 00:01:05,774
[tires screeching]

28
00:01:05,857 --> 00:01:07,067
[Audrey, in English] <i>Oh my God!</i>

29
00:01:07,150 --> 00:01:08,234
[Audrey] Oh, are you okay?

30
00:01:08,318 --> 00:01:09,486
[in English] I'm so sorry!

31
00:01:09,569 --> 00:01:10,653
Atoy?

32
00:01:10,737 --> 00:01:12,363
PREVIOUSLY

33
00:01:12,447 --> 00:01:13,406
[Ibyang] <i>There's a bad man there.</i>

34
00:01:13,490 --> 00:01:15,075
<i>He said he would pinch me.</i>

35
00:01:15,158 --> 00:01:17,410
<i>I said you'll deal with him.</i>

36
00:01:18,036 --> 00:01:19,621
I need your help.

37
00:01:19,704 --> 00:01:20,663
Janine ran away!

38
00:01:20,747 --> 00:01:21,706
I'm chasing someone.

39
00:01:21,790 --> 00:01:24,000
This person I'm after is dangerous.
I need to get there--

40
00:01:24,083 --> 00:01:25,502
Atoy, Janine is our child!

41
00:01:29,547 --> 00:01:31,966
[music swells]

42
00:01:32,050 --> 00:01:33,468
What?

43
00:01:34,928 --> 00:01:36,137
What do you mean by "our child"?

44
00:01:36,763 --> 00:01:38,681
[Atoy] How about you?
Where's Janine's father?

45
00:01:39,766 --> 00:01:40,934
Is she my child?

46
00:01:41,017 --> 00:01:42,310
You're so assuming.

47
00:01:42,393 --> 00:01:43,436
Why?

48
00:01:44,020 --> 00:01:45,730
Was I the only one you had
a relationship with before?

49
00:01:45,814 --> 00:01:47,607
[pensive music playing]

50
00:01:47,690 --> 00:01:48,858
How did that…

51
00:01:50,693 --> 00:01:53,446
Then why did you lie to me
when I asked you?

52
00:01:53,530 --> 00:01:54,614
[in English] I'm… I'm sorry!

53
00:01:54,697 --> 00:01:57,075
Because I didn't want you
to be part of her life.

54
00:01:57,158 --> 00:02:00,453
You already have a foster child, right?
You already have a girlfriend!

55
00:02:01,037 --> 00:02:02,372
You're happy with your life.

56
00:02:02,455 --> 00:02:04,165
Hold on a second. Girlfriend?

57
00:02:04,249 --> 00:02:05,125
Girlfriend?

58
00:02:05,208 --> 00:02:07,043
- You have a girlfriend?
- Yes, Tonet is his girlfriend!

59
00:02:07,627 --> 00:02:09,921
That's why I didn't want
to mess up his life anymore.

60
00:02:10,004 --> 00:02:11,673
You? You?!

61
00:02:11,756 --> 00:02:13,341
Still, you shouldn't have lied to me

62
00:02:13,424 --> 00:02:14,551
when I asked you!

63
00:02:14,634 --> 00:02:16,344
And now you're telling me I have a child?

64
00:02:16,427 --> 00:02:17,512
Ah, we… we have a child?

65
00:02:17,595 --> 00:02:19,681
And how can I be sure she's mine?

66
00:02:20,265 --> 00:02:22,016
So now, where's the child?
Shouldn't she be with you?

67
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:23,393
Suddenly, she went missing!

68
00:02:23,476 --> 00:02:25,895
And then what? You'll just blame me?

69
00:02:27,021 --> 00:02:28,606
[in English] You know what?
I made a mistake.

70
00:02:28,690 --> 00:02:29,899
I wish I hadn't told you

71
00:02:29,983 --> 00:02:31,067
about your child.

72
00:02:31,693 --> 00:02:32,735
Wait--

73
00:02:32,819 --> 00:02:34,279
Wait, wait!

74
00:02:34,362 --> 00:02:35,488
You already have a child,

75
00:02:35,572 --> 00:02:37,699
and then you're dating Tonet?

76
00:02:37,782 --> 00:02:39,159
My sister is single!

77
00:02:39,242 --> 00:02:41,119
While you have excess baggage?

78
00:02:41,202 --> 00:02:43,955
[tense music playing]

79
00:02:44,706 --> 00:02:45,874
[in English] I'm wasting my time.

80
00:02:45,957 --> 00:02:47,333
If you won't help me,

81
00:02:47,417 --> 00:02:49,168
I'll look for Janine myself.

82
00:02:49,252 --> 00:02:51,129
- Wait, hold on.
- What do you want?!

83
00:02:51,212 --> 00:02:53,298
[music fades]

84
00:02:53,381 --> 00:02:54,465
I'll help you.

85
00:02:54,549 --> 00:02:57,051
[suspicious music playing]

86
00:02:57,135 --> 00:02:59,137
Oh-- Wait, wait.

87
00:02:59,220 --> 00:03:01,556
I don't want to ruin your reunion, okay?

88
00:03:01,639 --> 00:03:04,100
But, where's… What about the one
we're looking for?

89
00:03:04,183 --> 00:03:06,394
No, forget about him.
What's important is my daught--

90
00:03:06,477 --> 00:03:09,147
The little girl is more important.
Let's find the little girl.

91
00:03:09,898 --> 00:03:11,983
Do you have any idea
where she might've gone?

92
00:03:12,066 --> 00:03:14,068
She used to live around here.

93
00:03:14,152 --> 00:03:16,571
So I thought maybe she went back here.

94
00:03:16,654 --> 00:03:18,448
[in English] Or she should be
somewhere here.

95
00:03:18,531 --> 00:03:20,199
Okay, here's what we'll do. Let's split up

96
00:03:20,283 --> 00:03:21,993
so we can cover a bigger area.

97
00:03:22,076 --> 00:03:23,286
You go here. I'll go here.

98
00:03:23,369 --> 00:03:24,329
Emerson, you stay here.

99
00:03:25,413 --> 00:03:26,247
[music fades]

100
00:03:26,331 --> 00:03:27,290
How can I contact you?

101
00:03:27,373 --> 00:03:29,292
[sighs] Uh, wait.

102
00:03:29,375 --> 00:03:32,545
[tense music playing]

103
00:03:33,963 --> 00:03:35,673
Perfect. Maybe she's still here.

104
00:03:37,175 --> 00:03:38,635
[in English] Text me.

105
00:03:38,718 --> 00:03:40,094
Okay, let's go!

106
00:03:43,389 --> 00:03:45,934
[Audrey] Janine! Janine!

107
00:03:46,017 --> 00:03:47,477
- Where should I look for her?
- [Audrey sighs]

108
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:48,603
[Audrey] Janine!

109
00:03:48,686 --> 00:03:49,729
Atoy!

110
00:03:49,812 --> 00:03:51,981
[sauve theme music playing]

111
00:03:52,065 --> 00:03:53,900
[motorcycle revving]

112
00:03:54,943 --> 00:03:55,818
[scratches]

113
00:03:57,904 --> 00:04:01,699
[sewing machine clacking]

114
00:04:02,575 --> 00:04:05,078
[gunshots blasting]

115
00:04:05,161 --> 00:04:07,372
[clicking]

116
00:04:07,455 --> 00:04:09,457
[snipping]

117
00:04:09,540 --> 00:04:11,417
[music swells]

118
00:04:11,501 --> 00:04:15,088
[electronic blipping]

119
00:04:20,510 --> 00:04:21,594
Why?

120
00:04:21,678 --> 00:04:22,553
‪[dramatic sting]

121
00:04:22,637 --> 00:04:24,764
They say he has a client in Japan.

122
00:04:24,847 --> 00:04:25,974
Make him happy.

123
00:04:26,057 --> 00:04:27,892
Then your life will change.

124
00:04:27,976 --> 00:04:28,893
[cackles]

125
00:04:28,977 --> 00:04:29,811
[Ame] Sir!

126
00:04:29,894 --> 00:04:31,104
Sir, don't! Please!

127
00:04:31,187 --> 00:04:32,397
Sir!

128
00:04:32,897 --> 00:04:34,732
- [thuds, glass shattering]
- [crowd cheers]

129
00:04:34,816 --> 00:04:36,651
- Darryl!
- Whoo!

130
00:04:37,151 --> 00:04:39,028
[whooping]

131
00:04:39,112 --> 00:04:40,321
[suspicious music playing]

132
00:04:40,405 --> 00:04:41,990
- Why are we hiding?
- Shh!

133
00:04:42,073 --> 00:04:43,241
[inaudible]

134
00:04:43,324 --> 00:04:44,993
Keep quiet!

135
00:04:45,076 --> 00:04:47,745
We can't go near that man. He's dangerous!

136
00:04:47,829 --> 00:04:49,205
Why?

137
00:04:49,289 --> 00:04:50,665
Do you know him?

138
00:04:51,165 --> 00:04:52,625
[whispers] Do you know him?

139
00:04:52,709 --> 00:04:55,253
Yes! He's the one
who took me from the bar,

140
00:04:55,336 --> 00:04:56,838
to sell me to the Japanese.

141
00:04:56,921 --> 00:04:57,922
He's a bad man!

142
00:04:58,006 --> 00:05:00,174
[huffs]

143
00:05:00,675 --> 00:05:01,801
Really bad!

144
00:05:02,927 --> 00:05:04,887
I even saw him earlier,

145
00:05:04,971 --> 00:05:06,723
harassing the nun.

146
00:05:06,806 --> 00:05:08,057
Nun?

147
00:05:08,141 --> 00:05:09,267
‪Hmm-mm.

148
00:05:09,350 --> 00:05:13,354
I pity her because she's old.

149
00:05:14,063 --> 00:05:16,482
I thought she was Sister Norma

150
00:05:16,566 --> 00:05:18,484
because they're wearing the same habit.

151
00:05:18,985 --> 00:05:20,236
Are you sure?

152
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:21,863
Oh, I'm sure!

153
00:05:21,946 --> 00:05:24,282
[dramatic sting]

154
00:05:27,869 --> 00:05:29,829
[Ame] Uh, excuse me.

155
00:05:29,912 --> 00:05:31,998
Do you have a patient here who is a nun?

156
00:05:32,081 --> 00:05:34,208
Yes, but she was fetched
by her companions.

157
00:05:34,292 --> 00:05:36,627
Because the nun patient
is being transferred.

158
00:05:36,711 --> 00:05:37,628
Thank you.

159
00:05:37,712 --> 00:05:38,963
‪[tense sinister music playing]

160
00:05:42,967 --> 00:05:43,801
‪[dramatic sting]

161
00:05:49,932 --> 00:05:53,352
[foreboding music playing]

162
00:06:00,568 --> 00:06:01,736
[music fades]

163
00:06:01,819 --> 00:06:03,237
So, you think you can hide from me?

164
00:06:03,321 --> 00:06:04,572
You think I wouldn't find you?

165
00:06:04,655 --> 00:06:06,616
Come here. Come here, come here!

166
00:06:06,699 --> 00:06:08,326
- Help!
- Come here!

167
00:06:08,951 --> 00:06:10,703
- What are you doing?!
- Let go of me!

168
00:06:10,787 --> 00:06:12,830
- Don't move!
- Let go of me!

169
00:06:12,914 --> 00:06:15,625
- [grunts]
- [tense music playing]

170
00:06:15,708 --> 00:06:17,210
[groans]

171
00:06:18,878 --> 00:06:19,796
[groans]

172
00:06:21,297 --> 00:06:22,965
[music fades]

173
00:06:24,926 --> 00:06:25,885
Atoy.

174
00:06:26,511 --> 00:06:28,054
You know, I don't mind

175
00:06:28,137 --> 00:06:29,639
if you end up with my sister.

176
00:06:29,722 --> 00:06:32,725
At least… All I ask is that you tell me.

177
00:06:32,809 --> 00:06:34,310
So it's not just you who knows.

178
00:06:34,393 --> 00:06:35,895
So I won't be caught off guard.

179
00:06:35,978 --> 00:06:37,021
That's not true.

180
00:06:37,105 --> 00:06:38,815
Tonet and I are just pretending.

181
00:06:38,898 --> 00:06:40,900
Ah. [chuckles] Ah!

182
00:06:40,983 --> 00:06:42,735
- So, it's just fake news.
- [quirky music playing]

183
00:06:42,819 --> 00:06:44,570
You didn't make it clear.

184
00:06:44,654 --> 00:06:46,864
You know, even if we
don't end up as brothers-in-law,

185
00:06:46,948 --> 00:06:47,990
we can still be…

186
00:06:48,074 --> 00:06:50,785
I can still help you with your missions.

187
00:06:50,868 --> 00:06:52,620
For example, if you want something done,

188
00:06:52,703 --> 00:06:54,872
you can tell me! Make me your asset.

189
00:06:54,956 --> 00:06:56,165
Just tell me!

190
00:06:56,249 --> 00:06:57,917
I'll help you!

191
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:59,168
Not that you asked,

192
00:06:59,252 --> 00:07:00,211
but when I was a kid…

193
00:07:00,294 --> 00:07:01,129
[smirks]

194
00:07:01,212 --> 00:07:03,297
I was the local yellow-belter.

195
00:07:03,381 --> 00:07:05,758
I was the best at fighting.

196
00:07:05,842 --> 00:07:07,218
Those roundhouse moves.

197
00:07:07,301 --> 00:07:08,469
Those 45-degree moves like that.

198
00:07:08,553 --> 00:07:10,263
Or those roundhouse kicks.

199
00:07:10,346 --> 00:07:11,472
[sneaky sting]

200
00:07:11,556 --> 00:07:12,932
Atoy?

201
00:07:14,392 --> 00:07:15,935
Unbelievable.

202
00:07:16,018 --> 00:07:18,604
I've been talking nonstop here.

203
00:07:19,939 --> 00:07:21,190
[grunts and groans]

204
00:07:21,274 --> 00:07:22,442
[Emerson] My foot! Ouch.

205
00:07:22,525 --> 00:07:24,318
[groans] Ouch.

206
00:07:24,402 --> 00:07:25,528
Ouch.

207
00:07:25,611 --> 00:07:26,571
Janine?

208
00:07:27,613 --> 00:07:29,323
Huh? Ah, Ja-- Janine?

209
00:07:29,407 --> 00:07:31,409
[tense music playing]

210
00:07:32,869 --> 00:07:34,078
Janine is here!

211
00:07:34,162 --> 00:07:35,413
Oh, Atoy! Wait.

212
00:07:35,496 --> 00:07:36,831
- Ah-- Ouch!
- [Atoy] Janine!

213
00:07:36,914 --> 00:07:39,584
[tense music playing]

214
00:07:39,667 --> 00:07:41,252
[Emerson] Ouch, ouch.

215
00:07:41,335 --> 00:07:42,879
Wait, Atoy! Ouch!

216
00:07:42,962 --> 00:07:44,839
Ah, wait. Ouch.

217
00:07:45,465 --> 00:07:46,466
Wait.

218
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:54,390
[music fades]

219
00:07:55,016 --> 00:07:55,933
[Ibyang] Wait.

220
00:07:56,017 --> 00:07:57,810
Where are we going?

221
00:07:57,894 --> 00:08:01,189
We'll look for the nuns. Come on.

222
00:08:01,272 --> 00:08:03,316
They might have left already.

223
00:08:03,399 --> 00:08:05,818
We won't catch up to them.

224
00:08:05,902 --> 00:08:08,070
[suspicious music playing]

225
00:08:08,154 --> 00:08:10,239
We'll catch up to them. Come on.

226
00:08:12,867 --> 00:08:13,743
[Mongki] What now?

227
00:08:13,826 --> 00:08:15,119
Where's the girl you're chasing?

228
00:08:15,203 --> 00:08:17,455
[Aldrin] She eluded me.
Didn't you run into her?

229
00:08:17,538 --> 00:08:19,457
No! Where could she be?

230
00:08:20,124 --> 00:08:21,209
[Paldo] Boss!

231
00:08:22,251 --> 00:08:24,504
Boss, sorry. I was just busy.

232
00:08:24,587 --> 00:08:25,713
How are you?

233
00:08:25,796 --> 00:08:27,757
You're always like that. Do better.

234
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:30,468
You're always busy when there's work!

235
00:08:31,886 --> 00:08:33,679
[Paldo] Oh, sorry, Boss, um…

236
00:08:33,763 --> 00:08:35,056
Who are we looking for?

237
00:08:35,139 --> 00:08:36,557
A little girl.

238
00:08:37,475 --> 00:08:39,018
About nine years old.

239
00:08:39,101 --> 00:08:40,394
Wearing a light blue tank top

240
00:08:40,478 --> 00:08:42,021
and a light brown skirt.

241
00:08:42,104 --> 00:08:43,064
Boss?

242
00:08:43,606 --> 00:08:45,233
[in English] Nine years old?

243
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:47,026
[phone ringing]

244
00:08:48,402 --> 00:08:50,947
[suspicious music playing]

245
00:08:51,030 --> 00:08:52,281
Boss?

246
00:08:53,407 --> 00:08:54,951
What's the update on my order?

247
00:08:55,034 --> 00:08:56,869
It needs to be delivered later.

248
00:08:57,828 --> 00:08:59,789
Aldrin already has a target, Boss.

249
00:08:59,872 --> 00:09:01,749
It will be delivered.

250
00:09:01,832 --> 00:09:04,335
Hurry up. I'm getting embarrassed
in front of the client.

251
00:09:04,418 --> 00:09:05,962
[music continues]

252
00:09:09,048 --> 00:09:10,591
Boss is pissed.

253
00:09:10,675 --> 00:09:12,677
Find your target.

254
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:14,345
I'll go there. You go here.

255
00:09:15,596 --> 00:09:17,181
I'll go around there, Boss.

256
00:09:27,275 --> 00:09:29,235
Hey! Stay here!

257
00:09:31,028 --> 00:09:32,446
Hold this.

258
00:09:35,199 --> 00:09:37,201
Push me, so we'll go faster.

259
00:09:37,785 --> 00:09:38,911
- Okay?
- Okay.

260
00:09:40,580 --> 00:09:41,914
Ready, Big Sis Ame?

261
00:09:41,998 --> 00:09:43,291
[in English] Ready.

262
00:09:43,374 --> 00:09:46,877
[soft rock music playing]

263
00:09:49,547 --> 00:09:50,756
[nun 1] <i>Let's hurry.</i>

264
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:52,508
That man looking for Sister Norma

265
00:09:52,592 --> 00:09:54,510
might see us!

266
00:09:54,594 --> 00:09:56,804
I have a bad feeling about him.

267
00:09:57,388 --> 00:10:00,808
Sister, this trip will just be
a bit long, okay?

268
00:10:00,891 --> 00:10:02,476
But don't worry.

269
00:10:02,560 --> 00:10:05,062
You're with us. We won't abandon you.

270
00:10:05,146 --> 00:10:06,856
[muttering]

271
00:10:06,939 --> 00:10:09,233
[ominous music playing]

272
00:10:09,900 --> 00:10:13,863
She was like that earlier too.
I don't know why.

273
00:10:13,946 --> 00:10:15,656
[nun 1] Do you want something, Sister?

274
00:10:15,740 --> 00:10:17,158
Are you in pain?

275
00:10:17,241 --> 00:10:18,409
[mutters]

276
00:10:18,492 --> 00:10:20,202
I'm really sorry, Sister.

277
00:10:20,286 --> 00:10:22,872
We really don't understand.

278
00:10:22,955 --> 00:10:24,582
Don't you want to leave?

279
00:10:24,665 --> 00:10:25,833
[muttering]

280
00:10:25,916 --> 00:10:27,585
[tense music playing]

281
00:10:34,675 --> 00:10:35,843
[door clicks shut]

282
00:10:35,926 --> 00:10:36,761
[squeals]

283
00:10:36,844 --> 00:10:38,554
[man] Get in position! Catch it!

284
00:10:38,638 --> 00:10:39,555
[squeals]

285
00:10:39,639 --> 00:10:42,308
[exclaiming and applauding]

286
00:10:42,391 --> 00:10:44,268
[lively chattering]

287
00:10:44,352 --> 00:10:46,896
[cheering and applauding]

288
00:10:54,278 --> 00:10:56,072
Damn it!

289
00:10:56,155 --> 00:10:57,740
Didn't you see someone passing?!

290
00:10:57,823 --> 00:10:59,325
You saw that we were playing,

291
00:10:59,408 --> 00:11:00,534
and you're going to walk there?

292
00:11:00,618 --> 00:11:01,911
[girl] Are you dumb, bro?

293
00:11:02,578 --> 00:11:04,163
What, huh?

294
00:11:04,246 --> 00:11:05,623
What did you say, huh?!

295
00:11:05,706 --> 00:11:06,582
Ah! What did you say?!

296
00:11:06,666 --> 00:11:07,500
[clamoring]

297
00:11:07,583 --> 00:11:08,918
Ah, wait!

298
00:11:09,001 --> 00:11:10,628
You think we won't fight back, huh!

299
00:11:10,711 --> 00:11:12,380
Girls, beat him up!

300
00:11:12,463 --> 00:11:13,964
[clamoring]

301
00:11:14,048 --> 00:11:15,257
- [woman 1] Ouch!
- [overlapping chatter]

302
00:11:16,842 --> 00:11:19,845
- [grunting]
- [clamoring]

303
00:11:21,722 --> 00:11:22,807
[music fades]

304
00:11:23,516 --> 00:11:24,558
Emerson.

305
00:11:24,642 --> 00:11:25,768
Paldo!

306
00:11:25,851 --> 00:11:27,144
Oh? What are you doing here?

307
00:11:27,228 --> 00:11:28,270
- What are--
- You? What--

308
00:11:28,354 --> 00:11:29,355
What are you doing here?

309
00:11:29,438 --> 00:11:30,898
You, what are you doing here?

310
00:11:30,981 --> 00:11:32,566
You're not from here.

311
00:11:33,609 --> 00:11:35,569
I visited a friend.

312
00:11:36,070 --> 00:11:37,321
Ah.

313
00:11:37,405 --> 00:11:38,614
What… What happened to you?

314
00:11:38,697 --> 00:11:40,324
- Why…
- Ah, oh! Yes.

315
00:11:40,408 --> 00:11:43,577
No, because we were chasing a criminal.

316
00:11:43,661 --> 00:11:45,079
Atoy and I chased a criminal,

317
00:11:45,162 --> 00:11:48,374
but I got hit by… by a child.

318
00:11:48,457 --> 00:11:50,835
Uh, this child turned out to be…

319
00:11:50,918 --> 00:11:53,337
the child of Atoy's fling

320
00:11:53,421 --> 00:11:55,214
who looks like Mama Mary.

321
00:11:55,881 --> 00:11:57,800
You mean Atoy is here?

322
00:11:59,385 --> 00:12:00,302
Atoy?

323
00:12:00,970 --> 00:12:02,012
Yes, you just said it.

324
00:12:02,096 --> 00:12:03,681
- Did I say Atoy?
- [Paldo] Yes!

325
00:12:03,764 --> 00:12:06,183
[Emerson] Atoy? Is that you?

326
00:12:06,809 --> 00:12:08,519
Atoy, is that you!

327
00:12:08,602 --> 00:12:10,396
[smirks] What's this? Your new sideline?

328
00:12:11,105 --> 00:12:14,191
- Is this one of your secret missions?
- [Atoy] Shh. Keep quiet.

329
00:12:14,275 --> 00:12:15,818
It's a secret, right?

330
00:12:15,901 --> 00:12:17,027
They will know. You're loud.

331
00:12:17,111 --> 00:12:18,487
They'll know who we are.

332
00:12:18,571 --> 00:12:20,823
Uh, I didn't say Atoy. I didn't-- No.

333
00:12:20,906 --> 00:12:21,907
[Paldo] Huh?

334
00:12:21,991 --> 00:12:24,952
What I said was… The child!

335
00:12:25,035 --> 00:12:26,203
The child, I said…

336
00:12:26,287 --> 00:12:27,538
- [Paldo] Oh?
- Uh…

337
00:12:27,621 --> 00:12:28,998
The child who--

338
00:12:29,081 --> 00:12:31,417
who hit me, then…

339
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:34,211
That's it. I got hurt in my thigh.

340
00:12:34,295 --> 00:12:35,671
I chased that kid!

341
00:12:35,754 --> 00:12:36,964
[Paldo] A kid?

342
00:12:38,257 --> 00:12:39,592
You're chasing a child?

343
00:12:40,342 --> 00:12:41,719
What does she look like?

344
00:12:41,802 --> 00:12:45,931
Well… A girl…

345
00:12:46,015 --> 00:12:47,725
About nine years old. A mestiza girl.

346
00:12:47,808 --> 00:12:52,146
Wearing blue, a light brown skirt, that…

347
00:12:52,229 --> 00:12:53,814
It's this young girl.

348
00:12:54,315 --> 00:12:57,359
[clamoring]

349
00:12:58,068 --> 00:12:59,612
You won't stop bothering me, huh?

350
00:12:59,695 --> 00:13:00,905
[clamoring, screaming]

351
00:13:00,988 --> 00:13:02,198
What, huh?!

352
00:13:02,281 --> 00:13:05,159
[screaming and panicking]

353
00:13:05,242 --> 00:13:06,869
[girl] Let's get out of here!

354
00:13:06,952 --> 00:13:07,912
[girls squealing]

355
00:13:07,995 --> 00:13:09,497
Just relax, bro!

356
00:13:10,289 --> 00:13:11,290
Put down your gun.

357
00:13:11,373 --> 00:13:13,417
[tense stinging]

358
00:13:15,085 --> 00:13:16,462
[in English] You relax!

359
00:13:16,545 --> 00:13:20,299
- Try to come near me, I'll shoot you!
- [muttering]

360
00:13:20,382 --> 00:13:21,717
This is serious, very serious.

361
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:24,637
[screaming and panicking]

362
00:13:25,221 --> 00:13:26,639
[gunshots]

363
00:13:26,722 --> 00:13:27,556
No one follows me, or else!

364
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:29,433
You think you can escape from me, huh?

365
00:13:29,517 --> 00:13:30,726
[energetic rock music playing]

366
00:13:30,809 --> 00:13:32,520
You're just tiring yourself out!

367
00:13:32,603 --> 00:13:34,104
- [music fades]
- [girls squeal]

368
00:13:35,064 --> 00:13:36,273
[energetic rock music playing]

369
00:13:45,950 --> 00:13:46,992
[group] Wow!

370
00:13:47,076 --> 00:13:49,537
Excellent!

371
00:13:50,371 --> 00:13:51,497
[man] You deserve that!

372
00:13:53,082 --> 00:13:55,251
Do you know where this kid went?

373
00:13:55,834 --> 00:13:57,461
Uh, well…

374
00:13:58,045 --> 00:14:00,673
No. You know, Paldo, maybe you could…

375
00:14:01,257 --> 00:14:02,550
I'm confused, um…

376
00:14:02,633 --> 00:14:05,844
Can you come with me
to the clinic or a hospital?

377
00:14:05,928 --> 00:14:06,845
I'll just have my foot checked…

378
00:14:06,929 --> 00:14:08,264
No, no. I-I-I have an appointment.

379
00:14:08,347 --> 00:14:10,182
Please go with me.
We should also go to the police.

380
00:14:10,266 --> 00:14:11,475
I need to go there, because…

381
00:14:11,559 --> 00:14:12,726
- It hurts…
- I'll just put you in a taxi,

382
00:14:12,810 --> 00:14:14,812
- so you can go home.
- Yes, okay.

383
00:14:14,895 --> 00:14:15,938
- You'll cover that.
- Do you have any money?

384
00:14:16,021 --> 00:14:17,022
None.

385
00:14:17,523 --> 00:14:19,358
I'll just give you some.
Let's go, let's go.

386
00:14:19,942 --> 00:14:21,443
[sneaky music playing]

387
00:14:23,571 --> 00:14:25,948
[pensive music playing]

388
00:14:27,241 --> 00:14:28,868
Wait, wait! Hold on, hold on!

389
00:14:28,951 --> 00:14:30,369
- Why?
- [Ame] Ah.

390
00:14:31,287 --> 00:14:33,289
We just wanted to talk to…

391
00:14:33,372 --> 00:14:36,125
Sister and the nuns.

392
00:14:36,208 --> 00:14:37,293
Oh, them?

393
00:14:37,376 --> 00:14:38,419
There they go!

394
00:14:38,502 --> 00:14:39,378
They already left.

395
00:14:39,461 --> 00:14:43,215
Uh, did they mention who…
uh, which nun left?

396
00:14:43,299 --> 00:14:44,717
Did they mention a name?

397
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:45,843
No, none.

398
00:14:48,512 --> 00:14:50,014
- Okay. Thank you.
- [man] Okay.

399
00:14:50,097 --> 00:14:51,140
Okay.

400
00:14:59,940 --> 00:15:02,067
- Hey, hey, hey!
- Is that it?

401
00:15:04,486 --> 00:15:06,322
Make sure you bring him
to the precinct, okay?

402
00:15:06,405 --> 00:15:08,198
Don't let him escape. He's a criminal.

403
00:15:08,282 --> 00:15:10,034
We'll handle it.
The police are on their way.

404
00:15:10,701 --> 00:15:12,411
Let's go. Stand up.

405
00:15:12,494 --> 00:15:13,579
Let's go.

406
00:15:15,039 --> 00:15:16,332
[Atoy] Janine?

407
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:19,793
[tense swoosh]

408
00:15:23,213 --> 00:15:24,298
Janine.

409
00:15:25,049 --> 00:15:26,216
[grunts]

410
00:15:30,012 --> 00:15:32,389
[grunts]

411
00:15:37,811 --> 00:15:39,480
[music fades]

412
00:15:40,856 --> 00:15:41,690
‪[inaudible]

413
00:15:49,406 --> 00:15:51,992
- [pensive music playing]
- [inaudible]

414
00:15:53,661 --> 00:15:55,371
[doctor, in English]
She's going to be okay.

415
00:15:55,454 --> 00:15:56,664
But to be sure,

416
00:15:56,747 --> 00:15:58,749
we also gave her a tetanus shot.

417
00:15:59,416 --> 00:16:01,293
[in English] We'll just wait
for her to wake up.

418
00:16:02,169 --> 00:16:03,963
[in English] I'll go ahead. Excuse me.

419
00:16:04,046 --> 00:16:05,172
Thank you.

420
00:16:07,049 --> 00:16:09,176
[muffled background chattering]

421
00:16:10,052 --> 00:16:11,303
My child…

422
00:16:13,597 --> 00:16:14,932
Looks like she's okay now.

423
00:16:17,810 --> 00:16:20,729
Thank you… Atoy.

424
00:16:25,067 --> 00:16:26,276
It's nothing.

425
00:16:28,070 --> 00:16:30,072
If I can help other people…

426
00:16:31,031 --> 00:16:32,908
of course, I can help my own daughter.

427
00:16:43,252 --> 00:16:46,422
Janine, dear.

428
00:17:00,853 --> 00:17:03,272
[pensive music playing]

429
00:17:03,355 --> 00:17:04,231
[gasps]

430
00:17:04,314 --> 00:17:05,774
Janine?

431
00:17:06,775 --> 00:17:07,776
[in English] Nurse.

432
00:17:08,277 --> 00:17:09,820
Nurse, my child is awake.

433
00:17:09,903 --> 00:17:11,989
Janine. Janine…

434
00:17:12,865 --> 00:17:14,324
Don't worry, okay?

435
00:17:14,408 --> 00:17:15,909
You're safe now.

436
00:17:15,993 --> 00:17:17,786
[mutters]

437
00:17:17,870 --> 00:17:19,246
Mommy is here.

438
00:17:20,205 --> 00:17:21,832
[sighs]

439
00:17:21,915 --> 00:17:23,208
Wait.

440
00:17:24,376 --> 00:17:26,170
You're Ibyang's father, right?

441
00:17:27,921 --> 00:17:29,006
[Janine] Why are you here?

442
00:17:29,506 --> 00:17:31,050
I don't like you.

443
00:17:31,967 --> 00:17:35,471
- Mommy, why is he here?
- Uh…

444
00:17:35,554 --> 00:17:37,347
Janine. Janine.

445
00:17:37,431 --> 00:17:40,184
You just don't understand, but…

446
00:17:41,727 --> 00:17:43,437
there's something you need to know.

447
00:17:44,021 --> 00:17:46,857
[sinister music playing]

448
00:17:46,940 --> 00:17:47,775
‪[dramatic stinging]

449
00:17:59,453 --> 00:18:01,914
Janine, I am the--

450
00:18:01,997 --> 00:18:04,124
He's the one who saved you, dear.

451
00:18:09,838 --> 00:18:12,257
[in English] We owe him your life.

452
00:18:26,105 --> 00:18:28,440
Uh, Nurse, we're just
going to have a talk.

453
00:18:28,524 --> 00:18:30,275
Please take care of Janine for now, okay?

454
00:18:30,359 --> 00:18:31,652
Janine, okay?

455
00:18:33,904 --> 00:18:35,739
[Atoy] You're okay now.

456
00:18:36,907 --> 00:18:38,367
You're okay now.

457
00:18:45,874 --> 00:18:47,376
[music fades]

458
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:49,253
What was that?

459
00:18:49,336 --> 00:18:51,046
Why don't we tell her yet?

460
00:18:51,130 --> 00:18:53,048
[in English] Not now, Atoy.

461
00:18:54,007 --> 00:18:56,176
I remember when I told her

462
00:18:56,260 --> 00:18:57,761
that I'm her mommy,

463
00:18:58,387 --> 00:18:59,805
she got confused.

464
00:19:00,889 --> 00:19:02,057
[pensive music playing]

465
00:19:02,141 --> 00:19:03,433
To be honest with you,

466
00:19:03,517 --> 00:19:06,228
we're both still figuring things out.

467
00:19:06,311 --> 00:19:09,815
So please, not now.

468
00:19:09,898 --> 00:19:10,732
[in English] Please.

469
00:19:10,816 --> 00:19:11,900
Then when?

470
00:19:12,651 --> 00:19:13,777
[in English] Soon.

471
00:19:14,736 --> 00:19:15,946
[in English] I promise.

472
00:19:17,781 --> 00:19:20,200
She will eventually know
you are her father.

473
00:19:28,834 --> 00:19:31,253
[music fades]

474
00:19:35,382 --> 00:19:38,010
[revving]

475
00:19:38,844 --> 00:19:40,971
[phone ringing]

476
00:19:41,054 --> 00:19:43,056
- [suspicious music playing]
- [phone beeps]

477
00:19:43,140 --> 00:19:44,349
Hello?

478
00:19:44,433 --> 00:19:45,601
Were the children delivered?

479
00:19:46,768 --> 00:19:48,312
[Mongki] Boss, there's a problem.

480
00:19:48,395 --> 00:19:50,606
Aldrin was picked up.

481
00:19:50,689 --> 00:19:51,690
What?

482
00:19:52,316 --> 00:19:54,276
Were the children taken?

483
00:19:54,359 --> 00:19:55,986
[Mongki] <i>No, Boss.</i>

484
00:19:57,112 --> 00:19:58,488
Stupid!

485
00:19:58,572 --> 00:20:00,699
I'm the one who gets blamed
by the clients for your stupidity.

486
00:20:00,782 --> 00:20:02,034
Why was he caught?

487
00:20:02,117 --> 00:20:04,077
They said some man interfered,

488
00:20:04,161 --> 00:20:05,913
who then helped the kid!

489
00:20:05,996 --> 00:20:07,539
Who?

490
00:20:07,623 --> 00:20:10,125
They said he's not from this place, Boss.

491
00:20:10,709 --> 00:20:12,294
Who is this man ruining my plan?

492
00:20:12,377 --> 00:20:13,462
Find out!

493
00:20:15,589 --> 00:20:17,132
Son of a--

494
00:20:18,842 --> 00:20:21,595
Sorry if what you're saying
is hard to believe.

495
00:20:21,678 --> 00:20:23,347
If… If I hadn't helped you,

496
00:20:23,430 --> 00:20:26,308
then I wouldn't know
the real situation, right?

497
00:20:26,808 --> 00:20:28,810
[in English] You just have to trust me.

498
00:20:30,020 --> 00:20:32,064
When Janine gets home…

499
00:20:33,315 --> 00:20:35,025
We can meet on the weekend.

500
00:20:35,567 --> 00:20:36,777
[in English] I'll text you.

501
00:20:37,277 --> 00:20:38,654
[Dmitri] Excuse me, Nurse.

502
00:20:38,737 --> 00:20:39,821
I'm looking for my grandchild.

503
00:20:39,905 --> 00:20:40,781
[receptionist] Sir, just a moment.

504
00:20:40,864 --> 00:20:41,865
[in English] Oh my god, it's my dad.

505
00:20:41,949 --> 00:20:43,033
- [Dmitri] Her name is Janine.
- He might see you!

506
00:20:43,116 --> 00:20:45,202
I… I don't want too many questions.

507
00:20:45,285 --> 00:20:47,287
Please, leave first.

508
00:20:47,371 --> 00:20:50,958
I'm not ready to talk about us yet.

509
00:20:51,041 --> 00:20:52,251
[in English] Go.

510
00:20:53,710 --> 00:20:57,673
[pensive music playing]

511
00:20:59,883 --> 00:21:02,678
I'll expect you
to keep your promise, okay?

512
00:21:13,814 --> 00:21:15,148
[in English] Dad!

513
00:21:15,232 --> 00:21:16,233
[in English] Hi!

514
00:21:16,733 --> 00:21:18,485
- Hello. She really, um…
- [in English] How is she? How is she?

515
00:21:18,568 --> 00:21:20,237
She's good. She's good. Come. Come.

516
00:21:23,365 --> 00:21:24,408
[Dmitri] Hey, grandchild!

517
00:21:25,117 --> 00:21:26,785
How are you, huh?

518
00:21:27,452 --> 00:21:30,539
[music fades]

519
00:21:32,207 --> 00:21:33,500
Oh? Hey.

520
00:21:34,334 --> 00:21:35,544
How's your child?

521
00:21:36,128 --> 00:21:37,170
She's okay now.

522
00:21:39,006 --> 00:21:41,717
[mellow music playing]

523
00:21:42,634 --> 00:21:44,303
Oh, if she's okay already,

524
00:21:44,386 --> 00:21:46,013
why do you look like that?

525
00:21:46,888 --> 00:21:49,141
Did you already tell her
you're her father?

526
00:21:49,641 --> 00:21:50,767
Not yet.

527
00:21:51,351 --> 00:21:52,519
[scoffs]

528
00:21:52,602 --> 00:21:54,563
Why haven't you told her?

529
00:21:55,814 --> 00:21:57,232
You don't want to, right?

530
00:21:58,066 --> 00:22:00,277
You don't want to handle
that responsibility yet.

531
00:22:00,360 --> 00:22:02,154
You still want to live like a bachelor.

532
00:22:02,237 --> 00:22:03,280
Whoo!

533
00:22:04,114 --> 00:22:05,115
[smirks]

534
00:22:23,633 --> 00:22:25,552
[Dmitri] Your grandfather is here.

535
00:22:25,635 --> 00:22:27,262
Don't be afraid.

536
00:22:27,345 --> 00:22:28,221
Okay?

537
00:22:31,058 --> 00:22:32,684
Come on.

538
00:22:34,519 --> 00:22:35,645
Wait!

539
00:22:35,729 --> 00:22:37,481
I'm still injured.

540
00:22:55,457 --> 00:22:57,542
- [Ibyang] Change your slippers.
- Why are you still awake?

541
00:22:58,919 --> 00:22:59,961
Oh, well.

542
00:23:00,045 --> 00:23:03,006
She doesn't want to obey me.
She said she'll wait for you.

543
00:23:05,300 --> 00:23:07,552
How was your mission, Master?

544
00:23:09,304 --> 00:23:10,972
Successful, right?

545
00:23:11,056 --> 00:23:12,516
Of course, it's you.

546
00:23:12,599 --> 00:23:14,101
[pensive music playing]

547
00:23:14,184 --> 00:23:17,854
You know, Tatoy, there was a man earlier.

548
00:23:17,938 --> 00:23:19,397
He's very arrogant!

549
00:23:19,481 --> 00:23:21,608
He picked a fight with a nun!

550
00:23:22,859 --> 00:23:24,736
Do you remember the man from the bar

551
00:23:24,820 --> 00:23:26,738
who wanted to sell me to the Japanese?

552
00:23:27,405 --> 00:23:29,950
He was at the hospital earlier.

553
00:23:30,742 --> 00:23:33,036
He was even picking on a nun.

554
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:35,831
I thought it was Sister Norma.

555
00:23:37,749 --> 00:23:40,502
Is this the nun who knows
Ibyang's real parents?

556
00:23:40,585 --> 00:23:42,087
Exactly!

557
00:23:42,879 --> 00:23:45,590
So, you want to find Sister Norma

558
00:23:45,674 --> 00:23:49,302
to ask her who my real parents are?

559
00:23:51,179 --> 00:23:53,723
I hope so, so we'll finally know.

560
00:23:53,807 --> 00:23:56,393
That's not needed anymore.

561
00:23:56,476 --> 00:23:58,478
I already have Tatoy!

562
00:23:58,562 --> 00:24:00,730
And he doesn't have a child,

563
00:24:00,814 --> 00:24:02,816
so I'll be his child!

564
00:24:04,025 --> 00:24:07,028
[melancholic music playing]

565
00:24:20,041 --> 00:24:22,669
[electronic blipping]

566
00:24:28,466 --> 00:24:29,718
[tense music playing]

567
00:24:29,801 --> 00:24:31,219
I'm staying quiet here.

568
00:24:31,303 --> 00:24:33,638
Then someone tells me
I actually have a child?

569
00:24:33,722 --> 00:24:35,724
Ibyang already treats you as her father.

570
00:24:35,807 --> 00:24:38,560
You should also prepare her
for what she'll feel.

571
00:24:38,643 --> 00:24:40,061
[Atoy] Is Audrey there?

572
00:24:40,145 --> 00:24:41,605
It's important he talks to her.

573
00:24:41,688 --> 00:24:44,900
[Emerson] <i>Better call your flakey boss!</i>

574
00:24:44,983 --> 00:24:45,901
Who is causing trouble here?

575
00:24:45,984 --> 00:24:47,277
[security guard] It's them, sir.

576
00:24:47,360 --> 00:24:48,445
You?

577
00:24:48,528 --> 00:24:50,697
I'll make a surprise for Tatoy.

578
00:24:50,780 --> 00:24:52,449
Why are you sulking there?

579
00:24:52,532 --> 00:24:55,452
Ibyang is so hopeful she'll be adopted.

580
00:24:55,535 --> 00:24:57,245
This is just our secret, okay?

581
00:24:57,329 --> 00:24:59,247
But Atoy already has a kid.

582
00:24:59,331 --> 00:25:00,498
Leave us alone.

583
00:25:00,582 --> 00:25:01,958
Don't cause trouble here anymore.

584
00:25:02,042 --> 00:25:03,793
Get out of here.

585
00:25:03,877 --> 00:25:05,503
Or do you want me to put you in a box?

586
00:25:05,587 --> 00:25:06,922
[Cita] Ah, Atoy!

587
00:25:07,005 --> 00:25:07,964
UP NEXT

588
00:25:08,048 --> 00:25:09,424
[Cita] Atoy…

589
00:25:09,507 --> 00:25:11,718
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

590
00:25:11,801 --> 00:25:14,888
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

591
00:25:14,971 --> 00:25:17,682
Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
